data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work in safe code without an `unsafe` block:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

The only gotcha is that `sizeof(nint)` / `sizeof(nuint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't fixed at compile time). Use `IntPtr.Size` / `UIntPtr.Size` instead if you need the element size in safe code.
